<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-01-20T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-01-20T19:00:00-05:00" n="757" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d757">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711F.1914/1–1747: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Panama</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-01-20T19:00:00-05:00">January
                                    20, 1947—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>30. It appears <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 33 Jan 17 <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">Fonmin</gloss> plan contains factors which this
                            Govt consistently has found basically objectionable. Dept most anxious
                            for progress on new defense agreement and thereafter to meet Panama’s
                            justifiable requests on other pending matters. Accordingly, Dept feels
                            it advisable send Murray Wise<note n="6" xml:id="d757fn1">Assistant
                                Chief, Division of Central America and Panama Affairs.</note> to
                                <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> with Dept’s instructions to
                            assist in pressing negotiation these matters. If this proposal agreeable
                            to you Wise would plan arrive Panama by Sun 26. Please advise
                            immediately.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>